# Dev Workflow

Use Makefile targets — do not invent ad-hoc commands.

## Start / stop

- Native backend (MIDI, macOS say): `make run`
- Full Docker stack: `make up`
- Stop everything: `make stop`
- Env bootstrap: `make setup` (copies `backend/.env.example`)

## Tests

- All: `make test`
- Backend only: `make test-backend` (pytest via `backend/run-tests.sh`, sets `OSC_DRY_RUN=true`)
- Frontend only: `make test-frontend` (vitest)
- After backend changes: run at least the affected test file under `backend/tests/`

## Debug / probe

- Signal drop analysis: `make analyze-signal-trace`
- Timeline visualization: `make visualize-logs` → `logs/show_timeline.png`
- Automated probe run: `make run-tryout` (requires running backend)

## Environment

- Secrets only in `backend/.env` — never commit
- Tests must use `OSC_DRY_RUN=true` (set automatically by `run-tests.sh` and `conftest.py`)
- Native backend uses repo-root `data/` and `logs/` (see `backend/run-native.sh`)

## CI parity

- Backend CI: ruff + pytest
- Frontend CI: lint + build + vitest
- Run frontend vitest locally even when only backend changed if Director/Teil2 timing is affected
